<p>The <code>action</code> tag handles form actions.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre>{open}action 'submit'{close}
  {open}!-- Executes when action=submit --{close}
  Form submitted!
{open}/action{close}</pre>

<h2>Form Example</h2>
<pre>&lt;form method="post"&gt;
  &lt;input type="hidden" name="action" value="save"&gt;
  &lt;button type="submit"&gt;Save&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/form&gt;

{open}action 'save'{close}
  Data saved!
{open}/action{close}</pre>

<h2>Multiple Actions</h2>
<pre>{open}action 'create'{close}
  Creating...
{open}/action{close}

{open}action 'delete'{close}
  Deleting...
{open}/action{close}</pre>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Actions are triggered by POST requests with matching action parameter.</p>
